-- Shares of Brazil telecom firms Oi and TIM jump on potential deal
-- 
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 09:17AM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, Aug 27 (Reuters) - Shares of Brazilian telecommunications firm Grupo Oi SA <OIBR3.SA> jumped on Wednesday after the company announced it had hired investment bank Grupo BTG Pactual SA <BPAC3.SA> to advise on a plan to win control of rival TIM Participacoes SA <TIMP3.SA>. [ID:nL5N0QX0T8]

